{"type":"message","id":"eb0dde5c","parentId":"03491a4b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:15:26.658Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5tcs0qiu7mbv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Conditional Content Analysis\n**Date:** 2026-03-24 1630  \n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\n\n## Hypothesis\n- Tokens with high CFI (≥0.9) but moderate frequency (60-120 range) may be:\n  - **Scaffolding**: Perfectly predictable but carry no causal weight\n  - **Genuinely causal**: Presence changes next-pulse research trajectory\n\n## Candidate Tokens\n\n| Token | Freq | CFI | Category |\n|-------|------|-----|----------|\n| compression | 199 | 0.995 | High freq, very high CFI |\n| causal | 162 | 0.981 | Moderate-high freq, very high CFI |\n| phase | 187 | 0.946 | High freq, high CFI |\n| cfi | 114 | 0.969 | Mid freq, high CFI |\n| strategy | 95 | 0.953 | Mid freq, high CFI |\n\n## Method\n\nFor each token T, split pulse pairs into:\n- **T-present**: pulses containing T\n- **T-absent**: pulses NOT containing T\n\nCompare next-pulse content between groups:\n- Topic distribution\n- Research direction changes\n- Action frequency\n\n## Expected Outcomes\n\n### If tokens are scaffolding (CFI only):\n- Next-pulse content statistically identical regardless of T presence\n- Tokens are constant-format artifacts encoded in state\n\n### If tokens are genuinely causal:\n- T-present group shows different next-pulse trajectories\n- Specific research directions correlate with T presence\n\n## Analysis Script\nSee `analysis/conditional_content.ps1`\n```\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774383326656}}
{"type":"message","id":"44f538da","parentId":"eb0dde5c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:15:33.510Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture. Let me summarize the pulse results.","thinkingSignature":"a3ccee58278584eb54065800e9491750d3e808945b4b198845d2f3848af3849f"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse 2026-03-24 16:14:45 — Summary**\n\n**What happened:**\n- Commit `9dae95b` — 4 files changed, +261/-84 lines\n- New pulse log created: `pulse_2026-03-24 161445.md`\n- Mutation `2026-03-24 161112.mutation` was **rejected** (renamed from `proposed/` → `rejected/`) — it was a proposal to create a `CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md` research doc, but the pulse decided against it\n\n**Key observation from the pulse:**\n> The conditional content analysis is the critical experiment to empirically separate CFI (Pattern Information) from true causal effects — analyzing whether pulses following token T-present vs T-absent show different research content quality.\n\n**Rejected mutation (2026-03-24 161112):** Proposed creating `research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md` to test whether high-CFI tokens like \"compression\", \"causal\", \"phase\" are scaffolding (pure pattern) or genuinely causal (change next-pulse trajectory). The pulse rejected this mutation — the analysis wasn't applied as a file mutation.\n\n**Current state:** 0 proposed mutations pending, actively working on the conditional content analysis concept as an in-pulse experiment rather than a doc mutation. The sandbox is in a research-exploration loop focused on the CFI vs causal distinction."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8732,"output":320,"cacheRead":16815,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25867,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774383326659}}
